It's not coming; it's here. It's time. He'll multiply it like the fish and the loaves.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
He'll multiply it like the wedding feast where he turned the water into wine.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
He'll multiply. If he did it once, he'll do it again. Don't put God in a box.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
Hallelujah. Thank you, Father, for President Trump. Thank you, Lord, as you protect him tonight.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.450
Thank you, Father, that the haters are always going to hate, but we believe, Father, that you rebuke the devourer for us and that he sleeps tonight.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.900
Whatever's keeping him up at night, God, I ask you to let him sleep so he doesn't sleep on the job whenever he's at a game or something they have to criticize him for.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
Thank you, Lord, that he gets good, restful sleep when it's time to sleep.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
And what would normally be like another person gets five hours of sleep, let it be like a good ten hours.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
Double it. If he gets five hours, double it, Lord, through his flesh like you did with Moses.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
You kept his body with the glory. I ask you, God, to let him have a visitation from you tonight.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.800
Touch President Trump, touch his marriage, bless Melania.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
Father, I thank you, Lord. There are things you show me about the marriage. We pray for the marriage.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
We pray for President Trump's marriage, and we ask you, God, to make it good, make it fresh, break down walls.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
Thank you, Lord. There's peace over Barron. There's joy on Barron.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
And, Father, that he'll find you. Same with Ivanka, same with Tiffany, and over Eric and Don Jr.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
We pray a revival in that family in Jesus' name. And even over Kai.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
And we call healing over the mother, the one that got diagnosed with cancer—over Kai, Don Jr.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
's ex-wife. We pray a healing over her. Breast cancer is gone, and it's not on the backbone.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.150
We call healing over her body, and we thank you, Lord, that she's delivered and healed and whole and well from cancer, and those kids will not be alone.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
Everything's going to be okay. All those children, we give God praise and glory.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
We pray healing over you tonight. You believe it for you? Delivered, healed, and whole and well in the name of Jesus.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
So, exciting times ahead, and we pray over President Trump's birthday, and over the games, and over the World Cup starting.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
Tomorrow, yep. In the next couple of minutes, it's the eleventh.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.950
I think the games start today in Los Angeles. And we thank you, Lord. Amen and amen.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
I believe we could keep—I could keep pushing, y'all, and keep y'all again for three hours, but it's not necessary.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
You can watch yesterday's video and we can keep praying, and we'll be back again to keep interceding for the nations.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Lord, we prayed longer tonight, did we not? Yeah, I believe so.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
I mean, let me see. Did you start praying earlier today, didn't you?

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.200
Yeah, I only talked for forty-some minutes today, I think. Right, yeah.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
So, I tried to pray more and not talk so much, but there's always a river to flow down.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.750
That's what I'm trying to tell you. You can pray for hours. You could be in here for five, six hours—boom, boom, boom, boom, boom.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
Especially when that river hits and that anointing flows. I could pray for hours.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
It's like, you know, but I know the videos go long, long, long for y'all.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
And I go, 'Well, I'm just thankful for every single one of you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
' Yeah, talk exactly, and two hours of prayer. So, I'm just so thankful for every single one of you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.600
I truly am. You show up every single day and you come and pray with me.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.200
And if it wasn't for you all, many hands make light work. I want you to always know I appreciate every single one of you. My gratitude is so great for you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
The pressure—what I tried to tell you all yesterday—is when you lead, there's something so different than leading in a prayer group.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
When you're leading and you feel the pull, it's like, you know, a boat anchor.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:12.250
It's like when you see those big massive chains and you're pulling it up out of the water and you see it and the anchor's massive on the huge boat like a big cruise ship.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.700
It's like pulling a chain and you're pulling in the spirit realm. I can feel it because we're praying for the nations.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
And it's not just like, 'Well, Father, I think you're praying for my family and you're showing me things around.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.400
' This is like a corporate. I can feel it when it comes out. And whenever the Lord said last night, he said, 'Push.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.850
' He kept—I could hear him, he was audible—'Push, push, push.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.350
' And I knew what he was saying: you've got to push above this, you've got to go above the hill.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.550
And that's what he's doing tonight. And I told him, I said, 'Pray.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.250
' I can feel when my wife's helping me pray. You can push above it.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
There's things he wants to show you. There's things that need to be uncovered.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
So, hallelujah. For many hands make light work. Isn't that wonderful? We're all a body. We're all moving together.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.900
So, we're here tonight and we're so thankful for every single one of you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.400
It just turned midnight in Central America. So, God bless you all. We love you. Enjoy your Thursday and we'll be back with you.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:10.850
We'll keep praying and keep believing and doing what we're called to do, one soul at a time, all doing what Jesus has called us to do, pushing and marching forward.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.650
Soldiers, thank you for being here. Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.300
Jesus loves you so much and we love you. God bless you and we'll see you again. Bye-bye.
